If you want to use the software commercially, you must obtain a separate commercial license from the Licensor.

0. Definitions
“Licensor” means the copyright holder(s) granting this License.
“Licensed Work” means the software and any associated materials distributed under this License.
“Covered Work” means either the Licensed Work or any modification, adaptation, or derivative of it.
“Distribute” includes making available, conveying, sublicensing, or otherwise providing copies of a Covered Work to any party.
“Network Use” means making a Covered Work available for use by others over a network (including providing it as a service).
“Non‑Commercial” means not primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation. Non‑Commercial use excludes (a) use by or for the benefit of a for‑profit entity (including internal use), (b) use in or for any product or service that is sold, licensed, leased, or otherwise monetized, and (c) use in advertising or to generate advertising, subscription, or usage revenue.

