  (d) make the Covered Work available for Network Use.
No patent rights or copyrights are granted for Commercial Use under this License.

2. Attribution Requirement
Any distribution, public use, or Network Use of a Covered Work must conspicuously give appropriate credit to the Licensor as the original author, include the project name, a link to the project home page (if available), and the text “Used under NC‑OSL‑A 1.0.”
  (i) In source form: retain all copyright notices, this License text, and a NOTICE file listing the attribution.
  (ii) In non‑source or user‑facing form (e.g., a GUI or web app): display “Powered by [PROJECT NAME] by [LICENSOR NAME]” in an about dialog, footer, or equivalent location accessible from all primary views. If space is limited (e.g., CLI), print the attribution in “--version” or startup output.
